anaging%20director%20and%20Washington%20policy%20analyst%20at%20Raymond%20James%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20the%20wider%20implications%20of%20political%20meddling%20with%20central%20bank%20policy%2C%20there's%20an%20ongoing%20example%20to%20point%20to%3A%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20has%20seen%20astronomical%20inflation%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20reaching%20as%20high%20as%2085%25%20in%202022.%20Inflationary%20pressures%20have%20since%20dropped%2C%20but%20consumer%20prices%20in%20Turkey%20are%20still%20up%20by%20about%2035%25%20over%20the%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurkey's%20president%2C%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdo%C4%9Fan%2C%20moved%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20Central%20Bank%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20Turkey%20in%202018.%20He%20has%20since%20fired%20five%20of%20the%20bank's%20leaders%E2%80%94all%20of%20whom%20he%20appointed%E2%80%94and%20has%20generally%20called%20for%20keeping%20interest%20rates%20low%2C%20though%20the%20bank%20went%20on%20a%20hiking%20spree%20in%202023%2C%20raising%20rates%20from%208.5%25%20as%20high%20as%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20country's%20benchmark%20short-term%20lending%20rate%20is%2045%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDominic%20Pappalardo%2C%20chief%20multi-asset%20strategist%20at%20Morningstar%20Wealth%2C%20said%20that%20while%20it's%20unlikely%20the%20US%20would%20see%20inflation%20at%20levels%20similar%20to%20Turkey%2C%20the%20situation%20should%20be%20a%20warning%20to%20the%20administration%20that%20Fed%20independence%20is%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20certainly%20think%20there%20are%20lessons%20to%20be%20learned%20there%20that%20the%20administration%20should%20be%20aware%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20Pappalardo%20said.%20%26quot%3BPerhaps%20somebody%20should%20be%20reminding%20President%20Trump%20of%20the%20direction%20things%20can%20go%20should%20he%20overpower%20Powell%20or%20the%20Fed%20or%20the%20checks%20and%20balances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20Turkey%2C%20there%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20other%20examples%20monetary%20policy%20gone%20wrong%20that%20are%20cautionary%20tales%20for%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20said%20Lukasz%20Tomicki%2C%20founder%20and%20managing%20partner%20at%20LRT%20Capital%20Management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTurkey%2C%20Argentina%20(until%20the%20most%20recent%20administration)%20and%20Venezuela%20are%20poignant%20examples%20of%20what%20happens%20when%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20subordinated%20to%20the%20executive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20the%20restraints%20of%20a%20politically%20independent%20central%20bank%2C%20politicians%20will%20always%20run%20substantial%20deficits.%20Once%20deficits%20become%20chronic%2C%20central%20banks%20are%20usually%20called%20in%20to%20buy%20unlimited%20amounts%20of%20government%20bonds%2C%20which%20inevitably%20leads%20to%20high%20and%20accelerating%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECentral%20banks%20rely%20on%20consumer%20and%20investor%20confidence%20to%20make%20effective%20policy%20changes.%20Credibility%20is%20key%2C%20and%20if%20there's%20a%20sense%20that%20the%20bank's%20leadership%20and%20policy%20decisions%20are%20unstable%2C%20the%20public%20may%20become%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstagflation-recession-us-economic-outlook-inflation-growth-unemployment-torsten-slok-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworried%20about%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20start%20baking%20higher%20prices%20into%20their%20outlook%20for%20the%20economy%2C%20creating%20an%20inflation%20spiral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-fire-powell-fed-interest-rates-tariffs-recession-economy-outlook-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIf%20Trump%20were%20to%20fire%20Powell%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there's%20a%20risk%20of%20inflation%20rearing%20its%20head%20again%2C%20said%20Doug%20Peta%2C%20chief%20US%20investment%20strategist%20at%20BCA%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20would%20undermine%20confidence%20in%20the%20Fed's%20independence%2C%20and%20therefore%20it%20would%20likely%20lead%20investors%20to%20expect%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20inflation%20going%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaymond%20James'%20Mills%20also%20said%20he%20thought%20the%20ultimate%20result%20of%20firing%20Powell%20could%20have%20the%20opposite%20effect%20Trump%20wants.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20part%20of%20what%20I%20don't%20understand%20about%20the%20strategy%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20you%20could%20have%20a%20situation%20where%20if%20he%20gets%20the%20outcome%20on%20personnel%20that%20he%20wants%2C%20that%20he%20could%20have%20the%20exact%20opposite%20impact%20on%20rate%20that%20he%20wants%2C%26quot%3B%20Mills%20said.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20post-pandemic%20inflation%20surge%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20Powell%20and%20the%20Fed%20rapidly%20hiked%20interest%20rates%2C%20walking%20a%20tight%20rope%20between%20fighting%20inflation%20and%20preventing%20the%20labor%20market%20from%20weakening%20substantially.%20So%20far%2C%20he%20has%20achieved%20those%20goals%2C%20with%20inflation%20under%203%25%20and%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20at%204.1%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20tariffs%20have%20complicated%20things%2C%20however.%20The%20import%20taxes%20threaten%20to%20raise%20consumer%20prices%2C%20leading%20Powell%20to%20pause%20the%20rate-cut%20cycle%20he%20had%20started%20last%20year.%20The%20wait-and-see%20approach%20has%20angered%20Trump%2C%20who%20worries%20higher%20interest%20rates%20could%20spark%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-powell-fed-meddling-markets-investors-turkey-inflation-central-bank-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752831901000%2C%22visua