r-energy-in-indias-remote-villages-are-empowering-handlooms-rooftop-solar-solutions-micro-grids%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echampioning%20energy%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20grassroots-level%20projects%2C%20the%20duo%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20soon%20joined%20by%20the%20third%20co-founder%20Prasad%20Kulkarni%20%E2%80%94%20was%20keen%20to%20electrify%20Gumla%20by%20harnessing%20the%20Sun%E2%80%99s%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20years%2C%20this%20concept%20would%20be%20christened%20the%20%E2%80%98solar%20microgrid%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20three%20years%2C%20the%20communities%20of%20Gumla%20watched%20a%20simple%20idea%20calcify%20into%20an%20impact%20that%20touched%2021%20villages%3B%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20their%20lives%2C%20800%20households%20experienced%20uninterrupted%20power%20supply.%20But%2C%20setup%20counts%20weren%E2%80%99t%20the%20only%20yardsticks%20of%20success%3B%20the%20real%20accomplishment%20was%20the%20shift%20in%20the%20womenfolk%E2%80%99s%20routines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolar%20power%20breathed%20a%20sense%20of%20ease%20into%20their%20day.%20They%20could%20now%20visit%20their%20neighbours%20after%20dark.%20Overnight%2C%20the%20streets%20shed%20their%20foreboding%20avatars%2C%20now%20illuminated%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F256764%2Fmumbai-startup-electric-vehicle-features-charger-cost-install-magenta-street-light-ev-charging-solutions-solar-energy-india-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar-powered%20street%20lights%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20gave%20them%20a%20semblance%20of%20liberty.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnergy%20poverty%20often%20perpetuates%20outdated%20power%20dynamics%20%E2%80%94%20literally%20and%20metaphorically.%20And%20the%20success%20story%20of%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20electrification%20holds%20a%20mirror%20up%20to%20this.%20In%202019%2C%20when%20the%20district%20tasted%20a%2024%2F7%20power%20supply%20%E2%80%94%20through%20the%20collaborative%20efforts%20of%20Gram%20Oorja%20and%20NGO%20PRADAN%20%E2%80%94%20it%20did%20more%20than%20enable.%20It%20empowered.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhen%20the%20villagers%20take%20charge%20of%20the%20grid%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20access%20to%20an%20unbroken%20flow%20of%20electricity%20meant%20the%20women%20could%20breeze%20through%20their%20chores.%20No%20longer%20relegated%20to%20the%20home%2C%20they%20optimised%20the%20extra%20time%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20Village%20Energy%20Committee%20(VEC)%2C%20where%20they%20got%20to%20be%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20decisions%20that%20would%20become%20the%20bedrock%20for%20village%20development%20%E2%80%94%20from%20calling%20the%20shots%20on%20energy%20tariffs%20to%20assigning%20the%20operational%20logistics%20to%20an%20elected%20local%20operator.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fhome-garden-1-1752771702.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20women%20of%20Jharkhand%20have%20become%20an%20active%20part%20in%20the%20decision-making%20process%20regarding%20the%20solar%20microgrids%20%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fhome-garden-1-1752771702.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fhome-garden-1-1752771702-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fhome-garden-1-1752771702-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fhome-garden-1-1752771702-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fhome-garden-1-1752771702-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-471763%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20women%20of%20Jharkhand%20have%20become%20an%20active%20part%20in%20the%20decision-making%20process%20regarding%20the%20solar%20microgrids%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20take%20these%20meetings%20seriously.%20As%20Suchita%20Ba%2C%20who%20heads%20them%20in%20her%20village%20in%20Kudpani%20Girijatoli%2C%20Simdega%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20these%20meetings%2C%20we%20collect%20the%20monthly%20tariff%20of%20Rs%20100%20from%20each%20family.%20Initially%2C%20every%20family%20pooled%20in%20Rs%202%2C000.%20The%20money%20is%20a%20backup%3B%20if%20the%20microgrids%20need%20maintenance%2C%20we%20can%20pay%20for%20it%20ourselves.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuchita%20is%20a%20busy%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F418417%2Ftanveer-inamdar-treei-foundation-portable-solar-energy-solution-tribal-families%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earrival%20of%20%E2%80%98light%E2%80%99%20in%20her%20village%3C%2Fa%3E%20gave%20her%20a%20lot%20to%20do%2C%20such%20as%20making%20decisions%20on%20how%20it%E2%80%99s%20used.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20did%20not%20have%20electricity%20for%20years.%20And%20then%20one%20day%2C%20we%20did.%20Now%20our%20lives%20look%20very%20different.%20My%20children%20can%20study.%20It%20gave%20us%20access%20to%20so%20many%20more%20facilities.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20freedom%20came%20with%20responsibility.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20put%20our%20own%20money%2C%20we%20feel%20responsible%20for%20the%20microgrids.%20Another%20reason%20why%20we%20do%20this%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20grids%20help%20our%20children%2C%20too.%20We%20want%20them%20to%20also%20benefit%20from%20solar.%20We%20are%20saving%20for%20our%20future.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacked%20by%20Gram%20Oorja%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Gumla%20are%20turning%20into%20custodians%20of%20their%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20success%20of%20the%20model%2C%20Sameer%2C%20one%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20Gram%20Oorja%2C%20says%20it%E2%80%99s%20hinged%20on%20two%20key%20players%20%E2%80%94%20CSR%20grants%20(which%20help%20with%20capital%20costs)%20and%20tariffs%2C%20which%20cover%20the%20maintenance%20costs.%20The%20latter%20is%20as%20crucial%20as%20the%20former%20because%20they%20allow%20for%20a%20judicious%20use%20of%20the%20resources.%20This%20is%20important%2C%20he%20explains%2C%20as%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F268152%2Fmaharashtra-village-manyachiwadi-solar-gram-electricity-sustainable-women-success%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocals%20witness%20continuous%20power%20supply%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20tendency%20to%20view%20it%20as%20a%20rare%20indulgence.%20Tariffs%20ensure%20prudent%20use.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaking%20them%20a%20part%20of%20the%20process%20ensures%20that%20the%20model%20goes%20beyond%20a%20fleeting%20inclusion%20and%20instead%20sustains%20itself%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20Over%20the%20life%20cycle%20of%20the%20project%2C%20the%20village%20bears%20around%2060%20percent%20of%20the%20overall%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Gumla%2C%20a%20constant%20power%20supply%20guarantees%20more%20than%20just%20peace%20of%20mind.%20It%20also%20lends%20them%20a%20quiet%20confidence%20to%20start%20dabbling%20in%20economics%20beyond%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20comfortable%20with%20on%20home%20turf.%20Sameer%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CThrough%20solar%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20village%20can%20grow%20an%20extra%20crop%2C%20engage%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F467095%2Fsolar-dryer-based-business%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagricultural%20processing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20adopt%20dehusking%20machines.%20These%20things%20add%20to%20their%20income%3B%20they%20make%20the%20system%20more%20viable.%20So%20you%20see%2C%20with%20a%20subsidy%2C%20the%20project%20would%20run%20for%20around%20four%20years.%20But%20the%20idea%20is%20to%20make%20it%20run%20forever.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhen%20energy%20becomes%20an%20enabler%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHow%20can%20energy%20access%20transform%20the%20villages%20of%20India%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20Sameer%20and%20Anshuman%20bent%20their%20heads%20over%20the%20question.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20contextualise%20their%20concerns%2C%20we%20revisit%20a%202015%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%2C%20which%20underscored%20that%20even%20though%20India%20was%20officially%20declared%20100%20percent%20electrified%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20just%2010%20percent%20of%20homes%20in%20a%20village%20had%20to%20have%20electricity%20to%20meet%20the%20criteria%20%E2%80%94%2017%20percent%20of%20homes%20were%20still%20without%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20bothered%20them.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20ideating%20on%20the%20best%20way%20to%20create%20impact%20in%20the%20villages%2C%20we%20struck%20upon%20the%20idea%20of%20energy%20access.%20We%E2%80%99re%20talking%20about%20a%20time%20when%20fossil%20fuel%20prices%20were%20steadily%20rising.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20you%20had%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F418409%2Findia-solar-power-electricity-bill-savings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20renewable%20energy%20becoming%20more%20accessible%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20idea%20was%20to%20take%20both%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20the%20falling%20prices%20of%20renewable%20energy%20and%20the%20rising%20prices%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20%E2%80%94%20and%20create%20a%20social%20impa